# Build Policy — Incremental Close-Out Build

**Status:** Project policy (2026-07). At the **end of every completed task** that touched compile inputs, run an **incremental** Release build. CMake/MSVC recompiles **only changed** `.cpp` / headers / touched units — not a full clean rebuild.

## Task close (default — required when code changed)

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| `cmake --build build --config Release` after version bump / changelog | `cmake --build` mid-implementation unless compile check is needed |
| Re-use existing `build/` — changed sources only recompile | `cmake --preset default` on every task |
| Kill `PIPBONG.exe` before link (`LNK1104`) — `scripts/build-release.ps1` does this | Assume exe is fresh without a build |
| Run `cmake --preset default` only when `build/` is missing, then `--build` | Full clean rebuild unless user asks |
| Skip close-out build when the task changed **only** docs / `.cursor/rules` / changelog with **no** C++ or `CMakeLists.txt` sources | Run release packaging automatically |

**Command (preferred):** `.\scripts\build-release.ps1` from repo root (auto-configure if needed, kill exe, incremental `--build`).

**IDE / F5 (mandatory):** Ctrl+Shift+B and F5 use tracked `.vscode/` + `cmake.enabled: false` — see `.cursor/rules/ide-build-workflow.mdc` and AGENTS.md §3.1. **Do not** fix IDE issues by re-enabling CMake Tools configure-on-open.

Equivalent: `Stop-Process -Name PIPBONG -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; cmake --build build --config Release`

**Dev preset:** `PIPBONG_SKIP_WINDEPLOY=ON` — incremental links skip `windeployqt` (~3 s no-change / ~5–15 s single-file edits). Run `.\scripts\deploy-qt.ps1` once when DLLs beside the exe are missing.

A `CMakeLists.txt` **version bump** reconfigures CMake and regenerates `PipbongVersion.h` — only `Application.cpp` and `UpdateChecker.cpp` recompile (not the whole target).

## Distribution — user request only

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| `.\scripts\package-release.ps1` — build, deploy Qt + vcpkg DLLs, zip `build/Release/` → `dist/PIPBONG-win64.zip` | Assume a single portable exe |
| `.\scripts\create-github-release.ps1` — package + publish ZIP to **`Baegovda/PIPBONG-releases`** | Run release packaging at ordinary task close |

Ship the **ZIP** (exe + `PIPBONGUpdater.exe` + Qt/OpenCV DLLs). Users extract and run `PIPBONG.exe` from the folder.

## CMake preset

| Preset | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **`default`** | `x64-windows`, `build/`, dynamic DLL linking — **task close and daily dev** |

